      <h3>Basket vs. Oven-Style</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Basket Style:</strong> These are the most common and are great for quick, even cooking of foods you would typically deep fry. They require shaking or tossing the food halfway through.</li>
        <li><strong>Oven-Style:</strong> Often doubling as a toaster oven, these use racks instead of a basket. They are better for baking, toasting, and cooking larger items like a whole chicken or a pizza.</li>
